    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>A Resignation in the Church</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Peter J Riga letter recommends Bishop Wilton D Gregory as replacement for resigned Boston Archbishop Bernard Law</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Now that Pope John Paul II has accepted the resignation of Cardinal Bernard F. Law as archbishop of Boston, a successor who is squeaky clean must be appointed.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Now that Pope John Paul II has accepted the resignation of Cardinal Bernard F. Law as archbishop of Boston, a successor who is squeaky clean must be appointed.</p>
        <p>My recommendation is Bishop Wilton D. Gregory, the president of the United States Conference of Catholic Bishops. He is articulate, intelligent, of proven leadership and clarity of vision. Above all, he is free of taint of covering up abusive priests. He also happens to be black, which can help the image of the Catholic Church among African-Americans.</p>
        <p>Wilton Gregory would make a powerful figure as archbishop of Boston and restore much of the credibility of the Catholic Church lost in the clerical sex abuse scandals.</p>
        <p>PETER J. RIGA  Houston, Dec. 13, 2002</p>
      </block>
    </body.content>
